The paper deals with the complexity of approximating a graph parameter, specifically the vertex expansion. This falls under the area of computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from computational geometry (cs.CG) and information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses the Small Set Expansion (SSE) hypothesis, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and has applications in machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper's focus on finding subsets with certain properties suggests that it may also be relevant to subareas such as submodular optimization (cs.DS) and social network analysis (cs.SI).
